{"type":"message","id":"bbe97047","parentId":"0cfdde96","timestamp":"2026-05-19T03:07:13.461Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to integrate with Cursor. Let me think about what \"对接\" (integrate/connect) means here. They've installed and logged into Cursor and want me to connect with it.\n\nCursor is an AI-powered code editor. \"对接\" likely means they want me to be able to interact with Cursor somehow - perhaps through its API, MCP (Model Context Protocol), or some other integration mechanism.\n\nLet me think about what options exist:\n1. Cursor has MCP support - I could set up an MCP server that Cursor can connect to\n2. Cursor has a rules system (.cursorrules)\n3. Maybe they want me to use Cursor's background agent features\n\n\n4. The most practical approach would be MCP - either setting up OpenClaw as an MCP server so Cursor can use my tools, or setting up Cursor's MCP so I can interact with it\n\nI need to clarify what kind of integration they're looking for since there are several possibilities - whether they want Cursor to call my tools, or if they want me to work on code in their project through Cursor.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"主人，请问想怎么对接？Cursor 这边有几种玩法：\n\n1. **MCP 集成** — 在 Cursor 里配置 MCP Server，让 Cursor 能调用 OpenClaw 的工具（飞书、文件操作等）\n2. **Rules 配置** — 给 `E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon` 项目写 `.cursorrules`，让 Cursor 了解项目规范\n3. **Background Agent** — 用 Cursor 的后台 Agent 跑任务，我来协调\n4. **其他** — 你有具体想法？\n\n你希望是哪种方向？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openai-proxy","model":"giant-claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779160018638,"responseId":"chatcmpl-97606b1b-cba3-4cd6-9e3f-0b16dbe1f659"}}
