{"type":"message","id":"cad2b640","parentId":"0457ada2","timestamp":"2026-05-19T03:08:11.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user just replied \"3\" meaning they want option 3 - Background Agent. But looking at this more carefully, \"Background Agent\" in Cursor means using Cursor's background agents feature. Let me think about what this actually means for integration.\n\nCursor's Background Agent is a feature that lets you run AI agents in the background within Cursor. The integration would mean connecting OpenClaw/me with Cursor's agent system.\n\nActually, I should look into how Cursor's Background Agent works and how I can integrate with it. The main ways to connect would be through MCP (Model Context Protocol) - Cursor supports MCP servers, which could allow Cursor agents to call OpenClaw tools.\n \nSo the user wants me to use Cursor's background agent to handle the actual coding tasks while I coordinate and orchestrate from the outside. The technical approach would likely involve setting up an MCP server that Cursor can connect to for bidirectional communication, or possibly using SSH/API-based integration instead. I need to research how Cursor's Background Agent integration actually works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_vrtx_01EBpvLhDYRwcRvfZiXQwYfG","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"Cursor background agent MCP integration setup 2025"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openai-proxy","model":"giant-claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779160080583,"responseId":"chatcmpl-c703e3de-eb83-4578-bbd0-516e9c1c59fc"}}
