{"type":"message","id":"b256a24f","parentId":"6ff681cd","timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:30:04.069Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is replying to an interactive card, likely a feishu message card that was sent as part of the hotupdate workflow. They want to use this card as a notification template. But I don't have access to the interactive card content since it was sent through the feishu system and I'm only seeing `[Interactive Card]` in the context.\n\nLet me check the conversation history or feishu messages to find out what card they're referring to. It's likely the previous hotupdate notification cards that were sent with `hotupdate-ok` or `hotupdate-fail` templates.\n\nActually, looking at the context, the user replied to a message with ID `om_x100b6ff02707f0a0c2151ff6a40655c`. This might be a card that was sent by the hotupdate pipeline sub-agent. Let me search memory or check what happened.\n\nWait - looking back at the conversation flow, earlier when the Unity hotupdate completed, the sub-agent sent a message to the dev group with `hotupdate-ok` template. But that's just text, not a card. And the user might be referring to a different card.\n\nActually, I think the \"Interactive Card\" might be something sent by the feishu system itself (like the hotupdate pipeline's own notification to feishu). The user wants me to use that card as a template for future notifications.\n\nBut I can't see the content of the interactive card. Let me ask the user what the card content looks like, or check if there's any recent card-related data in memory/state.\n\nHmm, actually looking at it again - the sub-agent for the hotupdate pipeline mentioned \"飞书内部通知发送成功\" which might be a card sent by the Unity pipeline itself (not through my feishu_send_group script). That's probably the interactive card they're referring to.\n\nLet me just ask what the card looks like so I can recreate it in the feishu_send_group script.","thinkingSignatu