{"type":"message","id":"96eb53f8","parentId":"bf3e0f72","timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:34:04.401Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the session history, I can see the messages but I don't see a 19:16 card message in the recent 30 messages. The messages I see are from about 18:45 onward. The 19:16 card might be further back in the history.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user says it was \"19:16分发给我\" (sent to me at 19:16). That's the message where they replied to \"[Interactive Card]\" saying \"这个作为通知模版\". The \"[Interactive Card]\" is the card content - but OpenClaw shows it as \"[Interactive Card]\" placeholder because it can't parse the Feishu interactive card format.\n\nI need a different approach. Maybe I should use the Feishu API to retrieve the specific message content. Let me check if I can use the feishu API to get the message content by message_id.\n\nThe user replied to message `om_x100b6ff02707f0a0c2151ff6a40655c` (from the reply context). I can try to use the Feishu API to fetch this message and see its card JSON.\n\nActually wait, looking at the reply context from the user's message at 19:16:\n```\n[Replying to: \"[Interactive Card]\"]\n\n这个作为通知模版\n```\n\nThe \"Interactive Card\" is likely a card that was sent AS a reply or from the Feishu system itself. The Feishu API can retrieve message content. Let me try to use the feishu API to get the message.\n\nActually, I have the feishu app credentials. Let me write a quick script to fetch the message content.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QpCfi4jBaNU3QUEknBqS6353","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"\nconst appId = 'cli_a9458ff380b99ccb';\nconst appSecret = 'Qs3NVpthJUXVGYqT8eTVMc8t7DffxM1Z';\n\nasync function main() {\n  // Get token\n  const tokenRes = await fetch('https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ app_id: appId, app_secret: appSecret }),\n  });\n  const tokenData = await tokenRes.json();\n  console.log('Token:', tokenData.code === 0 ? 'OK' : 'FAIL', tokenData);\n  \n  if (tokenData.code !== 0) return;\n  const token = tokenData.tenant_access_token;\n\n  // Get recent messages to find the card from around 19:16\n  // First, check recent conversations\n  const listRes = await fetch('https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/messages?receive_id_type=chat_id&page_size=50', {\n    headers: { 'Authorization': \\`Bearer \\${token}\\` },\n  });\n  const listData = await listRes.json();\n  console.log('Recent messages:', JSON.stringify(listData, null, 2).substring(0, 5000));\n}\nmain().catch(console.error);\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":9212,"output":720,"cacheRead":66432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76364,"cost":{"input":0.00128968,"output":0.00020160000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0018600959999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003351376}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779190436219,"responseId":"f989eb1e-d73b-4ade-8319-5b93ac563f76"}}
