{"type":"message","id":"00e808bf","parentId":"b4358a64","timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:01:39.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to look at the pipeline's internal server name. Let me check the build log from earlier - I saw in the build #1083 logs that the dest value was `1v1_cehua2` and there were log entries showing paths like `/data/1v1_cehua2/`.\n\nThe pipeline has a variable called `dest` which maps to actual server directories. The full list of available dest values would be in the pipeline's variable configuration. Let me check what we saw earlier in the pipeline analysis.\n\nFrom the earlier sub-agent analysis, I saw:\n- dest options included: `1v1_qa`, `1v1_cehua2`, etc.\n- Build #1083 used `dest=1v1_cehua2`\n- Build #1084 (the one we triggered) used `dest=1v1_qa`\n\nBut the user is saying \"查看一下流水线里面的服务器名字\" - check the server names inside the pipeline. Maybe they're referring to the actual server directory names in the pipeline's variable dropdown/list?\n\nLet me look back at the pipeline data more carefully. In the detailed analysis, the sub-agent mentioned the pipeline variables but I don't think I saw the full dropdown list of dest options.\n\nActually, looking at the conversation again more carefully... The user keeps saying I'm getting the server names wrong. Let me think about what the actual server name is.\n\nFrom the build #1083, the log showed:\n- The recent build by 敖亚军 used `dest=1v1_cehua2` (策划服)\n- The directory in the build log was `/data/1v1_cehua2/`\n\nWhen the user said \"更新qa服\" - the `1v1_qa` directory corresponds to QA test server.\n\nI think the user is saying the server names inside the pipeline are the `dest` values like `1v1_qa`, `1v1_cehua2`, etc. - not the Chinese names like \"qa服\" or \"测试服\".\n\nSo when they say \"更新qa服\", I should look at the pipeline's available dest options, find what matches \"qa服\" (which is `1v1_qa`), and report back using that internal name.\n\nBut wait, they said \"查看一下流水线里面的服务器名字\" - check the server names inside the pipeline. Maybe I need to go to the pipeline page and look at the dest dropdown to see all available options.\n\nLet me spawn a quick Playwright session to check what dest options are available in the pipeline's build trigger form.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好的，我去流水线里看看 `dest` 变量的可选值有哪些 🌸"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_JKYqkWdeZNDLM6aesd9x4562","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node -e \"\nimport { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('devops_cookies.json','utf8'));\nasync function main(){\n  const b=await chromium.launch({headless:false});\n  const ctx=await b.newContext({ignoreHTTPSErrors:true});\n  await ctx.addCookies(cookies);\n  const p=await ctx.newPage();\n  await p.goto('https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/projects/yyzy/pipelines/p-f78c977835c84b71a6d58b4746cd1c4a',{waitUntil:'networkidle',timeout:30000});\n  await new Promise(r=>setTimeout(r,3000));\n  \n  // Get all select options and variable names\n  const vars = await p.evaluate(() => {\n    const selects = document.querySelectorAll('select');\n    const inputs = document.querySelectorAll('input');\n    const result = [];\n    \n    // Get select dropdowns\n    selects.forEach((s,i) => {\n      const label = s.closest('[class*=variable], [class*=param]') || s.previousElementSibling;\n      const options = Array.from(s.options).map(o => ({value: o.value, text: o.text}));\n      result.push({type:'select', label: label?.innerText || s.name || 'unnamed', options, index: i});\n    });\n    \n    // Get input fields near the trigger form\n    inputs.forEach((inp,i) => {\n      const label = inp.closest('[class*=variable], [class*=param]') || inp.previousElementSibling;\n      if(inp.type === 'text' || inp.type === 'hidden') {\n        result.push({type:'input', name: inp.name || 'unnamed', placeholder: inp.placeholder, value: inp.value, index: i});\n      }\n    });\n    \n    return result;\n  });\n  \n  console.log(JSON.stringify(vars, null, 2));\n  await new Promise(r=>setTimeout(r,5000));\n  await b.close();\n}\nmain().catch(e=>{console.error(e.message);process.exit(1);});\n\" 2>&1","timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":13207,"output":1105,"cacheRead":65536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79848,"cost":{"input":0.00184898,"output":0.00030940000000000004,"cacheRead":0.001835008,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0039933880000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779192086650,"responseId":"228eb981-6a49-4b65-b261-535e67eb030d"}}
