{"type":"message","id":"4a53c685","parentId":"d5cfa7c0","timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:20:51.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see the problem clearly! In the group chat, the user said \"@_user_1 更新qa服\" multiple times, and each time I responded with:\n- \"收到，开始更新测试服 🌸\" (WRONG - they said qa服, I said 测试服)\n- \"热更已完成，测试服已更新 ✅\" (WRONG - this is the Unity hotupdate, not the DevOps server update!)\n- \"QA服热更完成 ✅ 群通知已发出~\" (WRONG - 热更 is client, not server)\n\nSo the issue is that in the group chat, when the user said \"更新qa服\", my group chat session was triggering the **Unity client hotupdate** (\"更新测试服\" skill) instead of the **DevOps server update** (\"更新服务器\" skill).\n\nThe group chat is a different session from this direct chat. The group chat session might be:\n1. Using an older version of the skills (no memory of today's changes)\n2. Misinterpreting \"更新qa服\" as the original \"更新测试服\" skill\n3. Not having access to the updated MEMORY.md/COLLEAGUE_WHITELIST.md\n\nThis is a serious issue. Let me check:\n1. Whether the group chat session sees the same workspace files (yes, AGENTS.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md should be shared)\n2. Why it's interpreting \"更新qa服\" as the hotupdate skill\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the logs - the group chat session ran the Unity hotupdate (BAT file) and called the `feishu_send_group.mjs` with `hotupdate-ok` template each time the user said \"更新qa服\"! \n\nThis is because:\n1. The original \"更新测试服\" skill was set up first\n2. The skill description in `update-test-server` originally included \"更新qa服\" as a trigger\n3. The group chat session is interpreting \"更新qa服\" as the original hotupdate skill\n\nI need to:\n1. Acknowledge the issue to the user\n2. Fix the heuristic to ensure correct skill is triggered\n\nActually the bigger issue: when the user @s me in a group, I should treat \"更新qa服\" as the DevOps server update (1v1_qa), not the Unity hotupdate. Let me explain this to the user and check what needs to be fixed.找到原因了 😅\n\n刚才在群里 4 次都搞错了！主人说「更新qa服」时，我误以为是 **客户端热更**（跑了 Unity 流水线 + 在群里发「测试服已更新」），其实应该是 **服务端 DevOps 更新 1v1_qa**！\n\n**根因：** \n1. 群聊那个 session 是另一个独立的对话上下文，没经历我们这边的演进\n2. 群聊里我看到「更新qa服」，第一反应是查 skill 关键词，命中了原本「更新测试服」的别名（之前 skill 描述里塞过「更新qa服」当 trigger）\n3. 直接走了 Unity 热更流水线，没意识到「更新qa服」=服务端\n\n**修复方案：**\n- ✅ 今天我已经在 SKILL.md 里把「更新qa服」从 Unity 热更里删掉了\n- ✅ 新技能 `update-server` 才是「更新qa服」的正确处理者\n- ✅ TOOLS.md 和 MEMORY.md 也都明确了\n\n不过群聊那个 session 可能要等下次启动时才会加载新规则。下次主人在群里说「更新qa服」我会按服务端 DevOps 跑，不会再误判了～\n\n主人要不要我**重启 OpenClaw 网关**让所有 session 重新加载最新规则？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openai-proxy","model":"giant-claude-opus-4-7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779193228472,"responseId":"chatcmpl-2e3896eb-6c6d-411c-a436-1ad8c4206d96"}}
