{"type":"message","id":"843d08b0","parentId":"619a58b7","timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:23:20.992Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The user wants me to write a script that can restart OpenClaw, so when I need to restart, I can do it myself. The issue earlier was that `openclaw gateway restart` from within an exec call doesn't work well because the gateway is restarting WHILE handling my exec command.\n\nI need to write a script that:\n1. Schedules the restart to happen AFTER the current command returns\n2. Or uses some detached process mechanism\n\nLet me think about this. The idea is to spawn a child process that waits a few seconds, then runs the restart command, while the main process exits immediately. This way the gateway can finish responding before being restarted.\n\nIn Windows PowerShell, I can use `Start-Process` with a delayed command.明白！写一个延迟重启的脚本，避免我执行的时候卡死 🌸"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_vrtx_01PG9tRAUMFC3xyHUk3hXCb3","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\restart_gateway.ps1","content":"# 延迟重启 OpenClaw 网关\n# 用法: powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\\restart_gateway.ps1 [delaySeconds]\n# 默认延迟 3 秒后重启，让当前 exec 调用先返回再触发重启\nparam(\n    [int]$DelaySeconds = 3\n)\n\n$LogFile = Join-Path $env:TEMP \"openclaw-restart-$(Get-Date -Format 'yyyyMMdd-HHmmss').log\"\n\n# 在新进程里跑重启，主进程立即返回\nStart-Process powershell -ArgumentList @(\n    '-NoProfile',\n    '-WindowStyle', 'Hidden',\n    '-Command',\n    \"Start-Sleep -Seconds $DelaySeconds; `$env:PATH = `$env:PATH; openclaw gateway restart *>&1 | Tee-Object -FilePath '$LogFile'\"\n) -WindowStyle Hidden\n\nWrite-Host \"✅ 网关将在 $DelaySeconds 秒后重启\"\nWrite-Host \"📝 日志: $LogFile\"\nexit 0\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openai-proxy","model":"giant-claude-opus-4-7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason